column5: you mean I might get to use my new snowblower before the warranty is up?!?!?!
anywhere north east of toronto up to peterborough and a little north will mostly be rain..Yuck  http://www.theweathernetwork.com/weather/c...var1=1073994496
GBW  let's hope that your snowblower can be turned in a gas powered water pump if needed.

I already cleared 5" (deeper in the drifts) yesterday and they're saying another 1" today (got about 3/4" last night), PLUS 2 to 5 inches tomorrow (Orillia Area) and again Friday.  Been reading about a lot of guys with new blowers they haven't used yet this season - y'all are invited to try them out here!  I'm on my 3rd 2-1/2 gallon can of gas since the beginning of the year! Michael
used the blow the 2nd time this season a couple days ago... love TORO... blasts through it ... wouldnt mind some deep powder so i can use the sled in south ontario without driving to haliburton
fergedaboutit...winter is beat. a sled trip this weekend then give me spring and open water
Id have to agree...couple weeks left and ill gladly store the sled and the clam till next year.... SEE YAA !
Good to see a nice dumping otherwise the tributaries would be awfully low this spring. Its nice to have a good old fashioned blizzard every once and a while.
I have to say I'd rather have no snow....the commute east across the 401 in a blizzard sucks....lol
i'll ice fish until april.  then it's steelhead in new york state.  besides, i just got my sled!!
